To calculate average you could use the [`.reduce()`][1] method. 

But first you need to get all the salaries. `.getElementsByClassName` returns an [HTMLCollection][2]. To convert it to a list of numbers you could use the [spread syntax][3]: 
    
    const salaries = [...document.getElementsByClassName(&quot;employeeSalary&quot;)];

And then [map][4] this array to an array of numbers: 

    salaries.map(e =&gt; parseFloat(e.innerHTML))

Finally you use `.reduce()` to calculate the average: 

    .reduce((sum, cur) =&gt; sum += cur) / salaries.length;

